"title": "8236: doctrine, purpose of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8236",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Sound doctrine is intended to shape and mould the people of God for life and service in the world.</p>\n<h2>The purpose of doctrine for the individual</h2>\n<h3>It leads to repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:25\">2TI 2:25</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It leads to salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:16\">1TI 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:31\">JHN 20:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:21-1Cor1:24\">1CO 1:21–1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:14-2Tim3:15\">2TI 3:14–3:15</a></p>\n<h3>It is necessary for Christian maturity and effective service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:16-2Tim3:17\">2TI 3:16–3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:7-Ps19:8\">PSA 19:7–19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42-Acts2:43\">ACT 2:42–2:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:14\">EPH 4:11–4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:13-Heb5:14\">HEB 5:13–5:14</a></p>\n<h3>It makes possible a defence of the faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:15-1Pet3:16\">1PE 3:15–3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:2-Col2:4\">COL 2:2–2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:3\">JUD 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>It leads to enrichment and blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:1-Deut32:4\">DEU 32:1–32:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:7-Ps19:11\">PSA 19:7–19:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:97-Ps119:104\">PSA 119:97–119:104</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:10-Isa55:13\">ISA 55:10–55:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:1-Ezek3:3\">EZK 3:1–3:3</a></p>\n<h3>It leads to perfection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:28\">COL 1:28</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Doctrine as the basis of faithful ministry in the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:9\">TIT 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:6\">1TI 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:13-1Tim4:16\">1TI 4:13–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:13-2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:2\">2TI 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1\">TIT 2:1</a></p>",
